124. The verb sum is either an cautiore or a copulative oerb. It is an auxiliary verb when it helps to form some of the tenses of other verbs; it is copulative when it joins the subject to some other word which is used to describe the subject. The word thus used to describe the subject may be a noun or an adjective, and is called the compleuerat. If the descriptive word is a noun, it is called a predicamentum if it is an adjective, then it is called a predicate adjective.
